# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-incident-response
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Define the incident response workflow for kernel failures, node outages,
#   distcc failures, or cluster instability.
#
# Incident Response Workflow:
#
#   1. Detect
#      - cluster-health.yml
#      - cluster-dmesg-report.yml
#      - cluster-network-report.yml
#
#   2. Triage
#      - Identify failing node(s)
#      - Check kernel logs
#      - Check distccd status
#
#   3. Contain
#      - Drain workloads (if needed)
#      - Disable distccd on unstable nodes
#
#   4. Remediate
#      - Roll back kernel
#      - Restart services
#      - Replace failing hardware
#
#   5. Recover
#      - Validate cluster stability
#      - Re-enable distccd
#
#   6. Document
#      - Update incident log
#      - Record root cause
#
# Notes:
#   - This file defines the authoritative incident response workflow.
# =============================================================================
